cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment analysis of customer reviews, which is a natural language processing task. Additionally, the proposed model uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in NLP tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is often used in information retrieval systems to help users find relevant content. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the proposed model is a neural network-based approach for sentiment analysis. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category as sentiment analysis is a common application of AI techniques. 

Finally, cs.DL (Deep Learning) is a possible sub-category as the proposed model uses a deep neural network architecture.
